# Finding 013
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Client/server validation duplication
- File + line(s): `apps/jskit-value-app/src/app/state/alertsStore.js:44-55`, `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/alerts/service.js:50-70`
- Why it can drift/fail: `normalizeTargetUrl` is duplicated in both client store and server service with similar but not identical validation logic. This creates two sources of truth for the same rule.
- Concrete impact: Client and server can accept/reject different values over time, leading to inconsistent behavior or unexpected failures.
- Exact remediation: Centralize target URL validation in a shared module (e.g., `apps/jskit-value-app/shared/alerts/validation.js`) and use it on both client and server.

